Class FullyInlineUnicodeBNodeIV<V extends BigdataBNode>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IInlineUnicode, IV<V,String>, IVCache<V,String>, Serializable, Comparable<IV>, org.openrdf.model.BNode, org.openrdf.model.Resource, org.openrdf.model.Value

    public class FullyInlineUnicodeBNodeIV<V extends BigdataBNode>
extends AbstractBNodeIV<V,String>
implements IInlineUnicode
    Class for inline RDF blank nodes. Blank nodes MUST use a "short" Unicode ID to be inlined with this class, where "short" is the maximum length configured for the lexicon.

    Author:
    Bryan Thompson
    See Also:
    AbstractTripleStore.Options, Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • clone

        public IV<V,String> clone(boolean clearCache)
        Description copied from interface: IVCache
        Return a copy of this IV.

        Note: This method exists to defeat the hard reference from the IV to the cached BigdataValue in order to avoid a memory leak when the IV is used as the key in a weak value cache whose value is the BigdataValue. Therefore, certain IV implementations MAY return this when they are used for limited collections. The vocabulary IVs are the primary example. For the same reason, we do not need to recursively break the link from the IV to the BigdataValue for IVs which embed other IVs.

        Specified by:
        clone in interface IVCache<V extends BigdataBNode,String>
        Parameters:
        clearCache - When true the cached reference (if any) will NOT be set on the copy.
        Returns:
        The copy.
        See Also:
        (Thread-local cache combined with unbounded thread pools causes effective memory leak)

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Description copied from class: AbstractIV
        Return true iff the two IVs are the same point in the same value space. Points in different value spaces (as identified by different datatype URIs) are NOT equal even if they have the same value in the corresponding primitive data type.

        Note: The IV implementations typically DO NOT compare equals() with BigdataValues. Therefore you MUST NOT mix IVs and BigdataValues in the keys of a map or the values of a set.

        Specified by:
        equals in interface org.openrdf.model.BNode
